			<description><![CDATA[A Finnish AI startup, co-founded by an executive whose previous startup was sold to US semiconductor giant AMD, has raised €25m in an angel round, giving it a €325m valuation, just months after its la...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>A Finnish AI startup, co-founded by an executive whose previous startup was sold to US semiconductor giant AMD, has raised €25m in an angel round, giving it a €325m valuation, just months after its launch.</p>
<p>Helsinki-based <a href="https://qutwo.com" target="_blank">Qutwo</a> was co-founded by Peter Sarlin, whose previous startup Silo AI was sold to AMD for $665m in 2024. Qutwo has raised the round from angel investors, which include Legora’s Max Junestrand, Hugging Face’s Thomas Wolf and co-founders and owners from Schwarz Group, Index Ventures and Atomico, amongst others, it said.</p>
<p>Qutwo’s ambition is to build Europe's leading AI lab for the quantum era. Qutwo is building a software platform called Qutwo OS that, it says, helps companies get more out of AI, as quantum computing develops.</p>
<p>It says it has secured more than €20m in contracted revenue since its February launch. Qutwo was founded by Sarlin, Kaj-Mikael Björk, Sarlin’s co-founder at Silo AI, and Kuan Yen Tan, co-founder at Finnish quantum outfit IQM.</p>
<p>It says it already employs more than 50 scientists and engineers from the likes of Microsoft Research, UC Berkeley, and and Cambridge University. Sarlin said: “Qutwo’s angel round provides us more than just capital. We are at a moment that comes once in a generation.</p>
<p>“We’re honoured to be backed by founders and investors who have built and backed category-defining global companies, as we build the platform for the next AI paradigm."</p>
<p><br></p>
]]></content:encoded>
